  "name": "Witness the Legend",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "systems/pf1/icons/skills/yellow_38.jpg",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>At 8th level, as a move action, you can extol the virtues of yourself or an ally within 60 feet that you can see. This causes the target to shed light like a torch for 1 minute, and while the effect lasts, you can expend a daily use of your touch of glory domain ability as an immediate action to add 1d6 to an attack, saving throw, skill check, or ability check attempted by the target; for a roll to confirm a critical hit or save against a fear effect, you instead add 1d12. You can use this ability once per day at 8th level and one additional time per day for every 4 levels beyond 8th.</p>\n<p>This power replaces the Divine Presence power of the Glory Domain.</p>"
    },
